  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p>\r\n<p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p>\r\n<p>Skim through these steps</p>\r\n<p>Wash your fruit and veg</p>\r\n<p>Note: equipment and pan sizes vary. Ensure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 mins)</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p>\r\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of&nbsp;<strong>vegetable oil</strong>&nbsp;over the&nbsp;highest heat</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, rip the&nbsp;<strong>little gem leaves</strong>&nbsp;into rough, bite-sized pieces and add them to a large bowl</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Microwave</strong> the <strong>steamed brown basmati rice</strong> according to packet instructions</p>\r\n<p>Tip: if you're cooking two packets, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly!</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once your pan is <strong>very hot</strong>, add the <strong>beef strips</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and the<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (Can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p>\r\n<p>Cook for 1 min exactly, turning once halfway and making sure you don&rsquo;t overcook them</p>\r\n<p>Once done, transfer the <strong>beef strips</strong> to a plate to rest</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>fish sauce</strong>, <strong>soy sauce</strong>, <strong>hoisin sauce</strong> and <strong>rice vinegar</strong> with 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> in a small bowl &ndash; this is your <strong>dressing</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice the <strong>cucumber</strong> in half lengthways and slice finely</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>cucumber</strong>, <strong>heated rice</strong> and <strong>dressing</strong> to the bowl with the lettuce and give everything a good mix up</p>\r\n<p>Pick the <strong>mint leaves</strong> from their stalks</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/10-min-asian-beef-salad-with-crispy-onions/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Set the <strong>dressed salad</strong> in the centre of the table, ready to share</p>\r\n<p>Top with the&nbsp;<strong>beef strips</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;fried onions </strong>and<strong> mint leaves</strong>, and let everyone dig in</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
